n^2>n+1
(n+1)^2>(n+1)+1
(n+1)^2
\begin{align*} (n+1)^2&=n^2+2n+1\\ &>(n+1)+2n+1&&\text{by the induction hypothesis}\\ &>(n+1)+1&&\text{since }n>0\;. \end{align*}
\forall n\geq 2
n^2= n\cdot n>2\cdot1\cdot \sqrt{n}\geq n+1
n^2-n=n(n-1)>1
(n-1)^2>0\implies n^2>2n-1=n+n-1\ge n+1
n\ge 2
 n^{2} = n + 1 + \left\lbrack\left(n - {1 \over 2}\right)^{2} - {5 \over 4}\right\rbrack \geq n + 2\,,\qquad\qquad n \geq 2 
